verbs.description: appose (third-person singular simple present apposes, present participle apposing, simple past and past participle apposed)

description: Coined based on Latin appōnō, by analogy with compose, suppose etc.

verbs.description: appose (third-person singular simple present apposes, present participle apposing, simple past and past participle apposed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To place next or to or near to; to juxtapose.
(transitive) To place opposite or before; to put or apply (one thing to another).
